%22%3A%22Why%20a%20former%20Fed%20chief%20says%20the%20China%20trade%20deal%20creates%20more%20problems%20for%20Powell%20and%20the%20central%20bank%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Federal%20Reserve%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6824d415c6ad288d1480ee78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EU.S.%20Federal%20Reserve%20Board%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20speaks%20during%20his%20re-nominations%20hearing%20of%20the%20Senate%20Banking%2C%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20Committee%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%2C%20in%20Washington%2C%20U.S.%2C%20January%2011%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EBrendan%20Smialowski%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Fed%20risks%20being%20behind%20the%20curve%20when%20the%20economy%20turns%2C%20Bill%20Dudley%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20former%20New%20York%20Fed%20chief%20said%20the%20US-China%20trade%20deal%20extends%20tariff%20uncertainty%2C%20delaying%20action.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20US%20enters%20a%20recession%2C%20I'd%20expect%20rate%20cuts%20of%20200%20to%20300%20basis%20points%2C%26quot%3B%20Dudley%20said.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20are%20celebrating%20easing%20trade%20tensions%20between%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-today-china-trade-deal-tariffs-sp500-dow-nasdaq-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20and%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week%2C%20but%20one%20former%20central%20banker%20warns%20that%20it%20could%20derail%20monetary%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Bill%20Dudley%2C%20the%20former%20president%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20this%20week's%20tariff%20de-escalation%20could%20create%20more%20headaches%20for%20the%20Fed%2C%20and%20cause%20it%20to%20mistime%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-fed-interest-rate-cuts-trump-tariffs-powell-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einterest%20rate%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20officials%20wait%20too%20long%20and%20the%20economy%20stumbles%20into%20a%20recession%2C%20this%20would%20force%20them%20to%20cut%20rates%20by%20200%20to%20300%20basis%20points%2C%20he%20wrote%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fopinion%2Farticles%2F2025-05-14%2Fchina-trade-deal-doesn-t-solve-the-fed-s-problems%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20yet%2C%20the%20latest%20trade%20deal%2C%20which%20dials%20back%20tariffs%20for%2090%20days%2C%20could%20compel%20the%20Fed%20to%20hold%20back%20on%20taking%20action%20until%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20trade%20war%20is%20clearer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20wait%2C%20and%20because%20they%20are%20waiting%2C%20they're%20probably%20ultimately%20going%20to%20be%20late%2C%26quot%3B%20Dudley%20reiterated%20in%20a%20separate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Di73OpmSeET0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20TV%3C%2Fa%3E%20interview.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20not%20the%20Fed's%20fault.%20I%20would%20behave%20exactly%20the%20same%20way%20in%20this%20set%20of%20circumstances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20stocks%20are%20enjoying%20a%20streak%20of%20gains%20thanks%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-trade-deal-tariffs-trade-war-outlook-wall-street-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrade%3C%2Fa%3E%20optimism%2C%20few%20economists%20expect%20improving%20relations%20to%20completely%20reverse%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-april-cpi-tariffs-prices-trump-trade-war-economci-outlook-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisk%20of%20tariff-fueled%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20if%20duties%20come%20down%2C%20tariff%20rates%20are%20still%20high%20enough%20to%20spur%20price%20growth%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20should%20also%20understand%20that%20the%20US-China%20deal%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20trade%20war%20is%20over%3A%20instead%2C%20it%20has%20diminished%20reciprocal%20rates%20to%20more%20digestible%20levels%20for%2090%20days%20to%20allow%20for%20negotiations.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20pause%20only%20extends%20uncertainty%2C%20it%20doesn't%20kill%20it%2C%20Dudley%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDudley%20cited%20that%20the%20average%20effective%20tariff%20rate%20will%20likely%20end%20up%20at%2017.8%25%2C%20enough%20to%20increase%20price%20levels%20and%20unemployment%20by%201.7%20and%200.35%20percentage%20points%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20estimates%20are%20the%20opposite%20of%20what%20the%20Fed%20wants.%20In%20the%20near%20term%2C%20Dudley%20expects%20that%20it%20will%20have%20to%20hold%20off%20and%20remain%20patient%2C%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20inflation%20expectations%20%E2%80%94%20cutting%20too%20early%20might%20support%20economic%20growth%2C%20but%20it%20risks%20exacerbating%20price%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20patient%2C%20though%2C%20also%20entails%20risks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20Rising%20unemployment%20could%20lead%20to%20more%20layoffs%20as%20spending%20slows%2C%20eventually%20precipitating%20a%20recession.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-trade-tariffs-federal-reserve-recession-inflation-kugler-trump-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFed%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20know%20its%20late%20if%20it's%20responding%20after%20a%20sizable%20unemployment%20rate%20increase%2C%20Dudley%20told%20Bloomberg%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20probably%20won't%20get%20much%20clarity%20on%20inflation%2C%20growth%20and%20trade%20policy%20until%20September.%20If%20at%20that%20point%20it%20needs%20to%20reduce%20rates%2C%20it'll%20have%20to%20move%20aggressively%20to%20arrest%20the%20deterioration%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20given%20that%20the%20tariff-induced%20supply%20sho